{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|2Co|5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","chapter":5,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":1,"text":"For we know that if our earthly tent we live in is destroyed, we have a building from God, an eternal dwelling in the heavens, not made with hands.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":2,"text":"Indeed, we groan in this tent, desiring to put on our heavenly dwelling,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":3,"text":"since, when we are clothed, we will not be found naked.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":4,"text":"Indeed, we groan while we are in this tent, burdened as we are, because we do not want to be unclothed but clothed, so that mortality may be swallowed up by life.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":5,"text":"Now the one who prepared us for this very purpose is God, who gave us the Spirit as a down payment.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":6,"text":"So we are always confident and know that while we are at home in the body we are away from the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":7,"text":"For we walk by faith, not by sight.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":8,"text":"In fact, we are confident, and we would prefer to be away from the body and at home with the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":9,"text":"Therefore, whether we are at home or away, we make it our aim to be pleasing to him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":10,"text":"For we must all appear before the judgment seat of Christ, so that each may be repaid for what he has done in the body, whether good or evil.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":11,"text":"Therefore, since we know the fear of the Lord, we try to persuade people. What we are is plain to God, and I hope it is also plain to your consciences.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":12,"text":"We are not commending ourselves to you again, but giving you an opportunity to be proud of us, so that you may have a reply for those who take pride in outward appearance rather than in the heart.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":13,"text":"For if we are out of our mind, it is for God; if we are in our right mind, it is for you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":14,"text":"For the love of Christ compels us, since we have reached this conclusion, that one died for all, and therefore all died.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":15,"text":"And he died for all so that those who live should no longer live for themselves, but for the one who died for them and was raised.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":16,"text":"From now on, then, we do not know anyone from a worldly perspective. Even if we have known Christ from a worldly perspective, yet now we no longer know him in this way.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":17,"text":"Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation; the old has passed away, and see, the new has come!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":18,"text":"Everything is from God, who has reconciled us to himself through Christ and has given us the ministry of reconciliation.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":19,"text":"That is, in Christ, God was reconciling the world to himself, not counting their trespasses against them, and he has committed the message of reconciliation to us.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":20,"text":"Therefore, we are ambassadors for Christ, since God is making his appeal through us. We plead on Christ’s behalf, “Be reconciled to God.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":5,"verse":21,"text":"He made the one who did not know sin to be sin for us, so that in him we might become the righteousness of God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","chapter":5,"paragraphStarts":[1,6,11,16,20],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Our Future after Death"},{"beforeVerse":16,"text":"The Ministry of Reconciliation"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For we know that if our earthly tent we live in "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Pt 1:13","book":"2Pe","chapter":1,"verse":13,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" is destroyed, we have a building from God, an eternal dwelling in the heavens, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Eph 6:9","book":"Eph","chapter":6,"verse":9,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Php 2:10","book":"Php","chapter":2,"verse":10,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" not made with hands. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Col 2:11","book":"Col","chapter":2,"verse":11,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Pt 1:13","book":"2Pe","chapter":1,"verse":13},{"label":"Eph 6:9","book":"Eph","chapter":6,"verse":9},{"label":"Php 2:10","book":"Php","chapter":2,"verse":10},{"label":"Col 2:11","book":"Col","chapter":2,"verse":11}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Indeed, we groan in this tent, desiring "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 2:2","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" to put on our heavenly dwelling, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Pt 2:2","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:5:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"since, when we are clothed, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Other ms